# Changelog and Versioning

## Every Task (required)

Add bullet(s) under `[Unreleased]` in **AGENTS.md** section **11. Changelog and Version History** as you implement:

- `Added` — new features
- `Changed` — behavior or UX changes
- `Fixed` — bug fixes
- `Removed` — deleted features

Use English. Be specific (file/behavior), not vague.

**Changelog ≠ handover:** §11 records *what changed*; procedures for the next agent (GitHub, release, scripts, URLs) belong in **AGENTS.md §3 / §8 / §9** in the **same task**. See `.cursor/rules/immediate-handover.mdc`.

## Version Bump (mandatory — every completed user task)

**Before closing the task**, bump version. Do **not** leave work only under `[Unreleased]` with an unchanged `CMakeLists.txt` version.

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Increment `project(PIPBONG VERSION ...)` in `CMakeLists.txt` |
| 2 | Move all `[Unreleased]` bullets into `## [x.y.z] - YYYY-MM-DD` in **AGENTS.md** §11 |
| 3 | Leave empty `[Unreleased]` section |
| 4 | Update **Current version** at top of **AGENTS.md** |
| 5 | **Incremental build at task close** when C++/headers/`CMakeLists.txt` sources changed → `cmake --build build --config Release` (or `scripts/build-release.ps1`; configure with `--preset default` only if `build/` missing). Skip when docs/rules-only. Release ZIP (`package-release.ps1`) only if user asked for distribution. |

### Which segment to increment

| Type | Example |
|------|---------|
| **Patch** `0.3.0 → 0.3.1` | **Default — every completed user task** |
| **Minor** `0.3.x → 0.4.0` | New block type, major subsystem, user-facing milestone |
| **Major** `1.0.0` | Breaking project JSON format |

When in doubt, **patch bump**.

`Application.cpp` reads version from generated `PipbongVersion.h` (from `CMakeLists.txt` `PROJECT_VERSION`); do not hardcode version strings elsewhere.

Full policy: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — **§10 Versioning Policy**, **§11 Changelog**, **§3.1 IDE workflow**.
